    <section class="card">
      <h1>Terms</h1>
      <p>
        These terms apply to the public SafeShare website and the free web app.
        SafeShare is provided “as is”.
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        Short version: Use at your own risk. Check important links before you share them.
      </div>

      <h2>1) Service description</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>SafeShare is a browser-based tool that removes common tracking parameters from URLs.</li>
        <li>Cleaning is performed locally in your browser (local-first).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2) No legal or security guarantees</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>SafeShare is not an anonymity tool and does not guarantee privacy or security.</li>
        <li>Removing parameters may change how a link behaves. Some parameters can be functional (e.g. affiliate attribution, filters, sessions).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3) Your responsibility</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You are responsible for the links you share and for verifying that a cleaned link works for your use case.</li>
        <li>If a cleaned link fails, use a more conservative approach or keep necessary parameters.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4) Availability</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The service may change, be paused, or be discontinued at any time.</li>
        <li>No guaranteed uptime.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5) Intellectual property</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>SafeShare branding and website content are protected by applicable laws.</li>
        <li>Open-source components (if any) remain under their respective licenses.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6) Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions, corrections, or support, use the Help page.
      </p>

